page_id: S4-LNX-04
title: File watcher status
description: Linux inotify watcher status with C4-19 manual-rescan confirmation handoff.
status_card:
  - Status: Running / Paused / Error / Unavailable
  - Backend: inotify
  - Watching: /home/you/AreaMatrix
  - Watches: 128
  - Last event
  - Last sync
  - Last rescan
  - Pending events
  - Latest rescan session
  - Rescan preview
states:
  loading: Checking watcher status...
  empty: File watcher is not available for this repository.
  running: AreaMatrix is watching this folder through inotify.
  limit_exceeded: Linux has reached the inotify watch limit.
  permission_denied: AreaMatrix cannot watch this folder because of permissions.
  network_mount: This location may not report all file changes.
  path_missing: Choose the repository again or reconnect the drive.
actions:
  restart_watcher: LinuxWatcherStatusViewModel.RestartWatcherAsync
  run_rescan_now: LinuxWatcherStatusView.RunRescanNow
  export_diagnostics: LinuxWatcherStatusViewModel.ExportDiagnosticsAsync
  open_repository_folder: LinuxWatcherStatusViewModel.OpenRepositoryFolderAsync
  close: LinuxWatcherStatusView.Close
disabled_rules:
  restart_watcher: Disabled while Starting or backend unavailable.
  run_rescan_now: Disabled while snapshot missing, path missing, DB locked, Starting, backend unavailable, or manual rescan running.
safety:
  - The page calls record_watcher_health through LinuxWatcherStatusCoreBridge.
  - Run rescan now calls get_latest_scan_session and preview_manual_rescan before raising S4-X-07.
  - The page captures Linux inotify health in LinuxWatcherDiagnostics before recording the Core snapshot.
  - Run rescan now raises OpenRescanConfirmRequested with LinuxRescanConfirmRequest for S4-X-07 and never calls reindex directly.
  - Export diagnostics writes only status metadata under .areamatrix/generated/diagnostics.
  - Recent events are relative path samples only; file contents are not exported.
  - The page does not call sync_external_changes, set_fs_event_cursor, reindex_from_filesystem, or resume_scan_session.
  - The page never runs sudo, chmod, or modifies system inotify settings.
